properties.areaDesc: San Luis Obispo County Central Coast; Santa Barbara County Central Coast
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 26 at 11:09AM PST until January 28 at 5:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Large breaking waves of 9 to 12 feet this evening
building to 10 to 14 feet on Monday. Dangerous rip currents.

* WHERE...West to northwest facing shores along the Central
Coast.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 5 PM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...There is an increased risk for ocean drowning. Rip
currents can pull swimmers and surfers out to sea. Large
breaking waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and
rocks, and capsize small boats near shore.
properties.instruction:
Remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions, or stay
near occupied lifeguard towers. Rock jetties can be deadly in
such conditions, stay off the rocks.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 PM PST TUESDAY
